rest_of_day_open: It's the weekend now, so it should be good. We do have a Hurricane coming, so I should be concerned, but I'm not too concerned since I'm more inland. It will affect my plans if the weather gets too rough. If so, then we will have to stay in. Sad as that may be, we will have things to occupy ourselves.
critical_positive: She was a very good listener, but poor question asker. I did most of the talking and she did active listening with head nods. She did not do much sharing on her end. She would make a few small comments after I paused, but we did have moments of "silence."
critical_negative: She did not really ask questions about me. I voluntarily provided stories from her prompt of "what do you do?" and then I did most of the talking and provided stories with that. I would then allow her to start to share, but her answers were very brief and not detailed with story.

rest_of_day_open: Busy with work, but overall fine. I think I'll get to have conversations online with family which will be nice. I'd like to make an effort to be productive - my closet needs cleaning and sorting - but I'm not an internally motivated individual so I tend to put things off.
critical_positive: We were both willing to listen and find points in common that we could chat about. I generally take a back seat in conversation and let the other person do the majority of the talking, and my partner was more than willing to be the conversation lead, which was appreciated.
critical_negative: I sometimes didn't know how to react to what he was saying, or I didn't understand the reaction he was looking for. I also would have preferred to not talk about Coronavirus as it's overwhelmingly present in my life so as it is, but it is something that unites all of us.
